ARM GAS  /tmp/ccuB84o5.s 			page 18


 530:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****    ===================
 531:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 532:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       The Stop 1 mode is based on the Cortex-M33 Deepsleep mode combined with
 533:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       the peripheral clock gating. The voltage regulator is configured in low
 534:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       power mode. In Stop 1 mode, all clocks in the VCORE domain are stopped.
 535:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       The PLL, MSIS, MSIK, HSI16 and HSE oscillators are disabled.
 536:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       Some peripherals with the LPBAM capability can switch on HSI16 or MSIS or
 537:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       MSIK for transferring data. All SRAMs and register contents are preserved,
 538:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       but the SRAMs can be totally or partially switched off to further reduced
 539:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       consumption.
 540:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       The BOR is always available in Stop 1 mode.
 541:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
 542:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) Entry:
 543:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           The Stop 1 mode is entered by using the HAL_PWREx_EnterSTOP1Mode()
 544:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           function.
 545:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
 546:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (++) PWR_STOPENTRY_WFI: enter Stop 1 mode with WFI instruction.
 547:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (++) PWR_STOPENTRY_WFE: enter Stop 1 mode with WFE instruction.
 548:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
 549:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) Exit:
 550:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           Any EXTI line configured in interrupt mode (the corresponding EXTI
 551:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           interrupt vector must be enabled in the NVIC). The interrupt source
 552:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           can be external interrupts or peripherals with wakeup capability.
 553:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           Any peripheral interrupt occurring when the AHB/APB clocks are present
 554:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           due to an autonomous peripheral clock request (the peripheral vector
 555:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           must be enabled in the NVIC)
 556:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           Any EXTI line configured in event mode.
 557:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
