 633:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /**
 634:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief  Enter the whole system to Stop 1 mode.
 635:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note   Stop 1 offers the largest number of active peripherals and wakeup
 636:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         sources, a smaller wakeup time but a higher consumption.
 637:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note   Stop mode achieves the lowest power consumption while retaining
 638:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the content of SRAM and registers. All clocks in the VCORE domain
 639:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         are stopped. The PLL, the MSI (MSIS and MSIK) RC, the HSI16 RC and
 640:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the HSE crystal oscillators are disabled. The LSE or LSI is still
 641:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         running.
 642:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note   The system clock when exiting from Stop mode can be either MSIS up
 643:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         to 24 MHz or HSI16, depending on software configuration.
