 684:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note   In Stop 2 mode, all clocks in the VCORE domain are stopped. The PLL,
 685:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         MSIS, MSIK, HSI16 and HSE oscillators are disabled.
 686:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note   Stop mode achieves the lowest power consumption while retaining
 687:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the content of SRAM and registers. All clocks in the VCORE domain
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccuB84o5.s 			page 22


 688:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         are stopped. The PLL, the MSI (MSIS and MSIK) RC, the HSI16 RC and
 689:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         the HSE crystal oscillators are disabled. The LSE or LSI is still
 690:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         running.
 691:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @note   The system clock when exiting from Stop mode can be either MSIS up
 692:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *         to 24 MHz or HSI16, depending on software configuration.
 693:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @param  STOPEntry : Specifies if Stop mode is entered with WFI or WFE
 694:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *                     instruction.
