 982:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /** @defgroup PWREx_Exported_Functions_Group3 Voltage Monitoring Functions
 983:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief    Voltage monitoring functions
 984:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccuB84o5.s 			page 37


 985:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** @verbatim
 986:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 987:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                      ##### Voltage Monitoring Functions #####
 988:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 989:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 990:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       This section provides functions allowing voltage monitoring.
 991:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
 992:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     *** PVM configuration ***
 993:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     =========================
 994:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 995:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) The supplies (VDDA, VDDIO2 and VDDUSB) can be independent from VDD and
 996:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           can be monitored with four peripheral voltage monitoring (PVM):
 997:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
 998:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (++) The UVM monitors the USB supply VDDUSB. VDDUSBRDY indicates if
 999:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                the VDDUSB independent power supply is higher or lower than the
1000:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                VUVM threshold.
1001:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (++) The IO2VM monitors the PG[15:2] supply VDDIO2. VDDIO2RDY
1002:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                indicates if the VDDIO2 independent power supply is higher or
1003:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                lower than the VIO2VM threshold.
1004:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (++) The AVM1 monitors the analog supply VDDA. VDDA1RDY indicates if
1005:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                the VDDA independent power supply is higher or lower than the
1006:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                VAVM1 threshold.
1007:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (++) The AVM2 monitors the analog supply VDDA. VDDA2RDY indicates if
1008:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                the VDDA independent power supply is higher or lower than the
1009:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                VAVM2 threshold.
1010:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1011:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) Each PVM output is connected to an EXTI line and can generate an
1012:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           interrupt if enabled through the EXTI registers. The PVMx output
1013:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           interrupt is generated when the independent power supply drops below
1014:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           the PVM threshold and/or when it rises above the PVM threshold,
1015:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           depending on EXTI line rising/falling edge configuration.
1016:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1017:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) Each PVM can remain active in Stop 0, Stop 1, Stop 2 modes, and the
1018:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           PVM interrupt can wake up from the Stop mode. The PVM is not
1019:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           functional in Stop 3 mode.
1020:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1021:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     *** VBAT charging ***
1022:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     =====================
1023:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
1024:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       When VDD is present, it is possible to charge the external battery on VBAT
1025:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       through an internal resistance.
1026:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       The VBAT charging is done either through a 5 kOhm resistor or through a 1.5
1027:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       kOhm resistor depending on the VBRS bit value in the PWR_BDCR2 register.
1028:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       The battery charging is enabled by setting VBE bit in the PWR_BDCR2
1029:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       register. It is automatically disabled in VBAT mode.
1030:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1031:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     *** Backup domain monitoring ***
1032:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     ================================
1033:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
1034:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       When the Backup domain voltage and temperature monitoring is enabled
1035:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (MONEN = 1 in the PWR_BDCR1 register), the Backup domain voltage and the
1036:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       temperature are monitored.
1037:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       If the Backup domain voltage monitoring internal tamper is enabled in the
1038:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       TAMP peripheral (ITAMP1E = 1 in the TAMP_CR1 register), a tamper event is
1039:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       generated when the Backup domain voltage is above the functional range.
1040:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       In case the Backup domain voltage is below the functional range,
1041:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       a Brownout reset is generated, erasing all device including Backup domain.
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccuB84o5.s 			page 38


1042:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1043:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     *** Backup domain battery ***
1044:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     =============================
1045:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
1046:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) To retain the content of the backup registers and supply the RTC
1047:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           function when VDD is turned off, the VBAT pin can be connected to an
1048:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           optional backup voltage supplied by a battery or by another source.
1049:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           The VBAT pin powers the RTC unit, the LSE oscillator and the PC13 to
1050:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           PC15 I/Os, allowing the RTC to operate even when the main power supply
1051:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           is turned off. The backup SRAM is optionally powered by VBAT pin when
1052:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           the BREN bit is set in the PWR Backup domain control register 1
1053:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           (PWR_BDCR1).
1054:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           The switch to the VBAT supply is controlled by the power down reset
1055:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           embedded in the Reset block.
1056:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1057:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       (+) After exiting reset, the USB Type-C (dead battery) behavior is enabled,
1058:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           which may have a pull-down effect on CC1 and CC2 pins. It is
1059:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           recommended to disable it in all cases, either to stop this pull-down
1060:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           or to handover control to the UCPD (the UCPD must be initialized
1061:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****           before doing the disable).
1062:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
1063:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** @endverbatim
